race.comment: LA REINE (11) resumed from a spell last start and was beaten 5.5 lengths over 1200m at Moonee Valley. She'd come off a try in a Group 3 and prior was narrowly beaten in an Open in Adelaide on debut. Fitter and capable of taking this out. TANANA (7)  filled a minor placing at Ballarat first up and then went close at Bendigo over 1400. Has the winkers on first time and a low gate and is sure to keep improving for a top yard. BRILLIANT BEAGLE (5) improved again narrowly beaten at Albury. Has the rail and should be at top. She won't have to improve much to feature. BRAZENGA (8) missed a nose at Hamilton and then had little support at Murtoa hit the frame two starts ago at Hamilton but ran below par last time when sixth and beaten 5.5 lengths over 1100m at Murtoa. May need the cut out of the track but this suits and it's hard to risk the premier stable. ALVIN (1) resumes and placed in a recent jumpout. Has the rail and has shown enough to consider.
